{"parse":{"title":"Jerry Lonecloud","pageid":37328190,"revid":814115604,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:JerryLonecloudNovaScotiaMuseum.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/JerryLonecloudNovaScotiaMuseum.jpg/220px-JerryLonecloudNovaScotiaMuseum.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"351\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/JerryLonecloudNovaScotiaMuseum.jpg/330px-JerryLonecloudNovaScotiaMuseum.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/00/JerryLonecloudNovaScotiaMuseum.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"376\" data-file-height=\"600\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:JerryLonecloudNovaScotiaMuseum.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Jerry Lonecloud</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Jerry Lonecloud</b> (July 4, 1854 \u2013 April 16, 1930)<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> was an entertainer, <a href=\"/wiki/Ethnographer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ethnographer\">ethnographer</a> and medicine man for the <a href=\"/wiki/Mi%27kmaq_people\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mi&#39;kmaq people\">Mi'kmaq people</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Nova_Scotia\" title=\"Nova Scotia\">Nova Scotia</a>.  He wrote the first Mi'kmaq <a href=\"/wiki/Memoir\" title=\"Memoir\">memoir</a>, which is entitled \"Tracking Dr. Lonecloud:Showman to Legend Keeper\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>  Historian Ruth Holmes Whitehead wrote, \"Ethnographer of the Micmac nation could rightly have been his epitaph, his final honour.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the 1880s, Lonecloud adopted the name \"Dr. Lonecloud\" during his career with <a href=\"/wiki/Medicine_Show\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Medicine Show\">American Medicine Shows</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Wild_West_Shows\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wild West Shows\">Wild West Shows</a>, including John Healy and Charles Bigelow\u2019s <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Kickapoo_Indian_medicine&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Kickapoo Indian medicine (page does not exist)\">Kickapoo Indian medicine</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Buffalo_Bill\" title=\"Buffalo Bill\">Buffalo Bill</a> Cody\u2019s Wild West Show and the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Kiowa_Medicine_Show&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Kiowa Medicine Show (page does not exist)\">Kiowa Medicine Show</a>. \n</p><p>As an ethnographer he worked extensively with historian and archivist <a href=\"/wiki/Harry_Piers\" title=\"Harry Piers\">Harry Piers</a>.\n</p><p>He and his family were living at <a href=\"/wiki/Tufts_Cove,_Nova_Scotia\" title=\"Tufts Cove, Nova Scotia\">Tuff's Cove</a> in Dartmouth during the <a href=\"/wiki/Halifax_Explosion\" title=\"Halifax Explosion\">Halifax Explosion</a>.  Two of his daughters were killed and he lost an eye.  He died in Halifax on April 16, 1930.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Legacy\">Legacy</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Jerry_Lonecloud&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Legacy\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Namesake of musical group Lone Cloud</li>\n<li>Namesake of Camp Lone Cloud Island</li>\n<li>A display in the Nova Scotia Museum of Natural History</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Link\">Link</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Jerry_Lonecloud&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Link\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.nsexplore.ca/lonecloud/Lonecloud.pdf\">Lonecloud - Nova Scotia Museum</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://novaojs.newcastle.edu.au/ojs/index.php/pes/article/viewFile/61/56\">Jason Price. \u2018The best remedy ever offered to the public\u2019:Representation and Resistance in the American Medicine Show. Popular Entertainment Studies, Vol 2, No 2 (2011)</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Jerry_Lonecloud&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.biographi.ca/en/bio/lonecloud_jerry_15E.html\">Biography - LONECLOUD, JERRY</a> Biographi.ca</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https://novascotia.ca/news/release/?id=20021011009\">https://novascotia.ca/news/release/?id=20021011009</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.biographi.ca/009004-119.01-e.php?&amp;id_nbr=8249\">Canadian Biography On Line</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1333\nCached time: 20180904191620\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.040 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.049 seconds\nPre